The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Balmer Lawrie amp; Co has posted a net profit of Rs 70.22 crore for the year ended March 31, 2007 against Rs 46.8 crore a year ago. Profit before tax was Rs 106.16 crore compared with Rs 80.85 crore in the year-ago period. Turnover increased to Rs 1,300 crore from Rs 1,252 crore. The company has declared a dividend of 135 per cent for the year.

 GEI Industrial Systems has posted a net profit of Rs 5.29 crore for 2006-07 against Rs 3.54 crore a year ago. Total income for the year stood at Rs 108.82 crore compared with Rs 69.27 crore in the year-ago period. 

 The Butterfly group has launched fuel efficient green label gas stoves. The products are co-branded with the Indian Oil Corporation.

